properties.description: St Germanus (380-448) was made a Bishop by St Patrick, and established this monastery in 428, one of the earliest in Cornwall and Britain. However, because he argued against the Pelagian heresy, he was working against many Celtic Christian ideas. What a place to start your journey!<br>St Germans became seat of the first Cornish Bishop, Conan, to bring Celtic and Roman ways together.
properties.name: St Germans Priory
